
This repository includes both lecture notes and project code for CS462 a class at Brigham Young University on large scale distributed systems. This edition of the class is taught by Phil Windley (http://www.windley.com) and focuses on using event-based architectures. 

This class will use Event Processing in Action by Opher Etzion and Peter Niblett as the text. 

Amazon: http://www.amazon.com/Event-Processing-Action-Opher-Etzion/dp/1935182218
Associated site: http://www.ep-ts.com/content/blogcategory/32/109/




If you learn nothing else in this class, you might at least learn to use Git. :)
